This document outlines how to install the SWMF on your system and how to
create and access the documentation.  To learn more about the SWMF, including
how to compile and run the code, please consult the user manual.  To install
the SWMF and create the user manual please follow the instructions below. 


###############
# Obtain SWMF #
###############

# Get the source code from cvs (UM only) or from the tar ball.

# !!! Getting SWMF from CVS !!!
# Set the CVS environment variables (with your user name)

setenv CVSROOT Your_User_Name_On_Herot@herot.engin.umich.edu:/FRAMEWORK
setenv CVS_RSH ssh

# Check out the SWMF_NEW distribution
cvs checkout SWMF_NEW  
cd SWMF_NEW

# !!! Opening the tar ball !!!
mkdir SWMF_NEW
cd SWMF_NEW
tar -xzf {path_to_file}/SWMF_v2.1.tgz


################
# Install SWMF #
################

# For several platform/compiler combinations installation is very simple.
# Some platforms require additional flags or have other compilers as
# an option. Choose the appropriate platform/compiler combination:

# !!! On Linux or Darwin with NAG F95 compiler,     !!!  
# !!! on the SGI Origin and on the Compaq machines  !!!
SetSWMF.pl -install

# !!! On the SGI Altix do the following !!!
SetSWMF.pl -install -c=ifort -m=Altix
module load intel-comp.8.0.070

# !!! On a Linux system with the PGF90 compiler !!!
SetSWMF.pl -install -c=pgf90

# !!! On Darwin using the xlf compiler !!!
SetSWMF.pl -install -c=xlf90

######################
# Create the manuals #
######################

# If you opened the tar file, you may have the manuals in the doc directory
# Check if you have the user manual in the doc/ directory
ls doc/SWMF.pdf

# Otherwise create PDF versions of the manuals in the doc/ directory.
make PDF

# Create HTML version of the manuals in the doc/HTML/ directory
make HTML

# Please note that creating both the PDF and HTML versions require that 
# LaTex be installed on your system.  In addition, creating the HTML
# version requires the latex2html utility 


####################
# Read the manuals #
####################

# All manuals can be accessed by opening the top index file doc/index.html
# The contents of the documents is briefly described in this file.
mozilla doc/index.html

# You may also read the PDF files directly with a PDF reader. 
